ed in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Roger de Vernai was born in 1250, in Blithfield, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Richard de Verney. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1277, in his hometown, at the age of 27."},"et":{"1250–1277":"1250–1277","1256–Male":"1256–Surnud","1274–Female":"1274–Surnud","–1306":"–1306","1221–1276":"1221–1276","1256":"1256","1277":"1277","1276":"1276","1221":"1221","1274":"1274","1250":"1250","1306":"1306","Madley, Herefordshire, England":"Madley, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Blithfield, Staffordshire, England":"Blithfield, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1250–1277":"1250–1277","1256–Male":"1256–Kuollut","1274–Female":"1274–Kuollut","–1306":"–1306","1221–1276":"1221–1276","1256":"1256","1277":"1277","1276":"1276","1221":"1221","1274":"1274","1250":"1250","1306":"1306","Madley, Herefordshire, England":"Madley, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Blithfield, Staffordshire, England":"Blithfield, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1250–1277":"1250–1277","1256–Male":"1256–Décédé","1274–Female":"1274–Décédée","–1306":"–1306","1221–1276":"1221–1276","1256":"1256","1277":"1277","1276":"1276","1221":"1221","1274":"1274","1250":"1250","1306":"1306","Madley, Herefordshire, England":"Madley, Herefordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Blithfield, Staffordshire, England":"Blithfield, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Roger de Vernai est né en 1250, à Blithfield, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de Richard de Verney. Il a eu au moins